FT  01 DEC 93 / Budget 93: Their Budget - The retailer
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Richard Woodall, 28.
Married with a one-year old child and another on the way. Has small mortgage
on three-bedroomed house in Wangford, Suffolk
Job: general manager of Asda superstore in Great Yarmouth, Norfolk. The
store occupies 46,000 sq ft and, with petrol, turns over pounds 500,000 a
week
Politics: last election voted Conservative and is a keen Tory supporter
Verdict: 'From a business point of view, it is good for us. There have been
no increases in VAT on books, foodstuffs, magazines or the like. Yes, there
has been an increase in petrol, but we are bery competitive in this area.
Personally, I am pleased there has been no increase in duties on beer and
spirits. I drive a company car, so I am not affected there. I am
particularly pleased there have been compensations for the VAT increases on
fuel. Overall, I am pleased and a little surprised.'
