FT  01 DEC 93 / Observer: Singular virtue
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Overheard in a schoolroom somewhere in England: 'Tell me Gubbins, why is
Christianity a good thing?'
'Because, sir, a man can only marry one woman, which is sometimes called
monotony.'
