FT  01 DEC 93 / Observer: Temperamental
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
An opera buff in the Bank of England's supervision department, which
monitors the health of banks, recently wrote to Jeremy Isaacs, the Royal
Opera House general director, complaining that a tenor in a recent
performance was neither 'in tune, in tempo or in Italian'.
Isaacs' response was that although the Opera House strives for perfection,
occasionally it falls short - which, he said, was not unlike the recent
experience of the Bank's supervision department.
