FT  01 DEC 93 / Observer: Shot in the toe
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Britain's education secretary John Patten obviously could not contain his
excitement at securing a 6.8 per cent increase in funding from the Treasury.
Why else should his department have released its budget news to the press
more than five hours before the chancellor was due to stand up?
However, it also meant that journalists had even more time to reflect on the
full ramifications of a near halving in the government's contribution
towards university students' tuition fees. Go to the back of the class,
John.
